  1742                                  ; create Buffer Descriptor List
  1743                                  ;
  1744                                  ; A buffer descriptor list is a list of pointers and control bits that the
  1745                                  ; DMA engine uses to know where to get the .wav data and how to play it.
  1746                                  ;
  1747                                  ; I set it up to use only 2 buffers of .wav data, and whenever 1 buffer is
  1748                                  ; playing, I refresh the other one with good data.
  1749                                  ;
  1750                                  ;
  1751                                  ; For the control bits, you can specify that the DMA engine fire an interrupt
  1752                                  ; after a buffer has been processed, but I poll the current index register
  1753                                  ; to know when it's safe to update the other buffer.
  1754                                  ;
  1755                                  ; I set the BUP bit, which tells the DMA engine to just play 0's (silence)
